      "side": 1,
      "message": "These comments helped tremendously.\n\nIs it important that we delay allocation until a Variable is first referenced?  If not, it might be easier to work with if we allocate one big array of skvm::Val ahead of time.  That\u0027d let us use pointers for indirection, I think making SkSL::(anon)::Value and this whole explanatory paragraph moot?  We could probably boil it down to,\n\n   // Each SkSL::Variable is backed by one (scalar) or more (vector, matrix) skvm::Vals.\n   SkSpan\u003cskvm::Val\u003e vals(const Variable\u0026);",
      "range": {
