      "writtenOn": "2020-12-14T22:15:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can tweak this comment some more. There isn\u0027t any long-term storage specific to Expressions, it\u0027s just that field access and array indexing can return a sub-set of the Vals from the variable that forms the (ultimnate) base of the expression. In that regard, if we did do the up-front allocation of Variables described above, this could also return SkSpan\u003cskvm::Val\u003e.\n\neg: the expression passed here is only ever a (struct) field access or array indexing operation, like:\n\nfoo.bar[1]\n\nThe returned location points to the middle of the range of Vals associated with \u0027foo\u0027.",
